    AdminPage class represents the user interface for the admin user.

    A page for viewing and managing Admin Requests.

    The AdminSetupPage class handles the setup process for creating an administrator account.

    Answer class represents an answer in the Question and Answer system.
    Answers
    Answers class represents the manager for all answer-related operations.
    DatabaseHelper
    The DatabaseHelper class is responsible for managing the connection to the database, performing operations such as user registration, login validation, and handling invitation codes.

    DatabaseHelper2 class provides database operations for the Question and Answer system.

    DatabaseHelper3 class provides database operations for the review system.

    FirstPage class represents the initial screen for the first user.

    InstructorHomePage class represents the home page for users with the instructor role.
    InvitationPage
    InvitationPage class represents the page where an admin can generate an invitation code.

    LogoutHelper class provides consistent logout functionality across all pages.
    MessageHelper
    Utility class to centralize messaging functionality
    Phase1AutomatedTests
    Phase1AutomatedTests.java This class contains comprehensive test suites for validating user account data including: - Username validation tests using FSM approach - Password evaluation tests using directed-graph approach - Email validation tests - Full name validation tests Each test suite is organized in nested classes for better organization and readability.
    Phase2AutomatedTests
    Phase2AutomatedTests.java This class contains test suites for validating the Question and Answer system functionality including: - Question creation and management - Answer creation and management - Feedback system - Question and Answer database operations

    ResetPasswordPage
    The ResetPasswordPage class provides an interface for users to reset their account password.
    Review
    Review class represents a review in the Question and Answer system.
    ReviewerHomePage
    ReviewerHomePage class represents the home page for users with the reviewer role.
    ReviewerPermissionsPage
    ReviewerPermissionsPage class represents the page for managing reviewer permissions.

    The RoleSelectionPage class allows users with multiple roles to select which role they want to play.
    SetupAccountPage
    SetupAccountPage class handles the account setup process for new users.
    SetupLoginSelectionPage
    The SetupLoginSelectionPage class allows users to choose between setting up a new account or logging into an existing account.
    StaffHomePage
    StaffHomePage class represents the home page for users with the staff role.
    StartCSE360
    StartCSE360 class is the main entry point for the CSE360 application.

    StudentHomePage class represents the home page for users with the student role.
